.\"	$NetBSD: hardware,v 1.1 2000/02/20 15:45:34 jun Exp $
A H/PC machine contains a keyboard and a touch screen and
generally has 8MB or more of RAM.  The port supports the HPC
form factor, as well as the H/PC Pro and PsPC (Palmsized PC)
form factors.

The following WindowsCE hardware is supported:
.de section
.	El
.	Pp
.	It Em \\$*
.	br
.	Bl -bullet -compact
..
.de item
.	It
\\$*
..
.Bl -tag -width Disks
.	It Em CPUs:
.	br
.	Bl -bullet -compact 
.		item VR4102-based: 
.		item VR4111-based: 
.		item VR4121-based: 
.		item TX3912-based: 
.		item TX3922-based: 
.	section RS232 interfaces:
.		item built in serial port (com).
.	section Network interfaces:
.		item PCMCIA ethernet card (ep/ne).
.	section Displays:
.		item LCD Display
.	section Input devices:
.		item Keyboard. 
.		item TouchPad. 
.	section Miscellaneous:
.		item Battery-backed real-time clock.
.	El
.El
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width (***)
.El
